Company description:  
  

BUMA's vision is to build a modern mining and rehabilitation company that
drives growth, sustainability and prosperity. This is supported by our core
values of safety, integrity, progress, collaboration and people.

With a strong commitment to safety, innovation and technology, BUMA pursues a
relationship-based long-term approach to ensure the mutual success of all
projects. Ensuring we provide value to our clients through all stages of
mining is a mainstay of our business and we have the expertise and equipment
to deliver total mining services to any surface operation.

  
  
Job description:  
  

We are now seeking an Operational Technology Systems Specialist to join our
Brisbane head office to maintain and provide advanced technical support for OT
platforms such as endpoint devices, applications and supporting systems,
servers, and network infrastructure. The role would suit someone with a strong
technical skillset and a comprehensive understanding of mining technology
systems.

Key Responsibilities:

  * Provide day-to-day technical advice, problem solving and support for operational technology systems. 
  * Monitor, troubleshoot and resolve advanced technical issues related to OT hardware, software and network connectivity. 
  * Install, configure, and upgrade OT endpoint devices, applications, servers, and network infrastructure. 
  * Develop detailed designs, technical documents, work instructions, procedures, and other documentation for BUMA knowledge bases. 
  * Manage the deployment of new applications and systems, ensuring that they are properly tested and integrated in coordination with the business. 
  * Visit sites on a routine basis to perform onsite maintenance and support activities and liaise with site stakeholders to understand technical challenges. 
  * Identify and explore technologies and innovations that could add value to the business. 

It is expected that this position works from the BUMA South Brisbane office
five days a week. Occasional travel to site is required.

  
  
Profile description:  
  

About You:

  * Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering or a related field. 
  * Experience in supporting operational technologies, preferably in the mining or heavy industries, and working with end-users. 
  * Broad level of IT proficiency, including competence in IT networks and cloud infrastructure, cybersecurity, data warehousing and wireless networking and mobility platforms. Recognised IT professional certifications are desirable. 
  * Strong attention to detail and problem-solving skills. 
  * Ability to work well in a team-oriented environment. 

To be considered for this opportunity please click "Apply Now" to submit your
application!

All final applicants for this position will be asked to consent to a police
check. Please note that people with criminal records are not automatically
barred from applying for this position. Each application will be considered on
its merits. Email applications and agencies are not accepted.

  
  
